The paper discusses the application of machine learning methods, specifically deep learning, for psycho-demographic profiling of internet users. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of digital footprints and the creation of psychological profiles also relates to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the potential impact on society, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential ethical implications of this technology, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
